###<a id='create-edge-tranport-node'></a>Create Edge Transport Node

1. Log in to the NSX Manager web interface (`https://<NSX Manager IP>`).

1. Go to Fabric > Nodes > Edges.

1. Select an Edge Node.

1. Click Actions > Configure as Transport.

  <img src="images/nsxt/nsx-misc/edge-transport-node-01.png">

1. In the General tab, enter the name: `edge-TN1`.

1. Select both Transport Zones:

	TX-Overlay (Overlay)
	TX-VLAN (VLAN)

  <img src="images/nsxt/nsx-misc/edge-transport-node-02.png">

1. Select the **Host Switches** tab.

1. Configure the first node switch as follows:

	Edge Switch Name: `hostswitch1`
	Uplink Profile: `edge-uplink-profile`
	IP Assignment: `Use IP Pool`
	IP Pool: `TEP-ESXi-POOL`
	virtual NICs: `fp-eth0` (corresponds to Edge VM vnic1--second vnic)

  <img src="images/nsxt/nsx-misc/edge-transport-node-03.png">

1. Click **Add New Node Switch**.

1. Configure the second node switch as follows:

	Edge Switch Name: `hostswitch2`
	Uplink Profile: `edge-uplink-profile`
	virtual NICs: `fp-eth1` (corresponds to Edge VM vnic2--third vnic)

  <img src="images/nsxt/nsx-misc/edge-transport-node-04.png">

1. Click Save.

##<a id='verify-tz-vlan'></a> Verify TZ-VLAN

1. Select Fabric > Nodes > Edges.

1. Verify that Controller Connectivty and Manager Connectivity are 'UP'.

  <img src="images/nsxt/nsx-misc/edge-transport-node-05.png">

1. Select Fabric > Nodes > Transport Node.

1. Verify that the configuration state is Success.

  <img src="images/nsxt/nsx-misc/edge-transport-node-06.png">

1. SSH to NSX Edge VM.

1. Run the following command and verify that the Edge transport node is "connected" to the Controller.

		nsx-edge-1> get controllers

1. Verify that the Edge transport node is "connected" to the Controller. For example:

	 	Controller IP    Port     SSL         Status       Is Physical Master   Session State  Controller FQDN
	  	10.40.206.4     1234   enabled     connected             true               up               NA       
	  	10.40.206.5     1234   enabled      not used            false              null              NA       
	  	10.40.206.3     1234   enabled      not used            false              null              NA

1. Repeat the same operations for the second Edge Transport Node (Edge-TN2).

1. Select Fabric > Nodes > Transport Nodes and verify Edge-TN2.

  <img src="images/nsxt/nsx-misc/edge-transport-node-07.png">

1. Select Fabric > Nodes > Edges and verify Edge-TN2.

  <img src="images/nsxt/nsx-misc/edge-transport-node-08.png">





